news.title: New software boosts Prayagraj civic body's tax collection
news.para: In the 2023, the total tax collection by the PMC was Rs 104 crores. Meanwhile, the PMC has extended the date of 10% rebate on house and water tax till Oct 31.

news.title: Pune civic body faces challenges in meeting Rs 2,400 crore property tax target for FY25
news.para: The civic administration needs to meet a target of Rs 2,400 crore by March 2025, a Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) official said. However, meeting the target appears to be a tough task for PMC due to issues like restrictions on recovery of tax in 34 merged areas.

news.title: Nashik civic body launches amnesty scheme for property tax defaulters
news.para: Under the scheme, defaulters can receive up to a 95% waiver on penalties if they clear all dues between Oct 1 and Nov 30. For those who pay their dues in Dec, an 85% penalty waiver applies, while a 75% waiver is available for payments made in Jan.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body tests e-Khata in two wards
news.para: To obtain a final e-Khata, citizens must submit additional details such as Aadhaar-linked KYC, GPS coordinates of the property, property photographs, the registered deed, encumbrance certificates dated from April 1, 2004, to the present and BESCOM (Bangalore Electricity Supply Company Limited) metre numbers.

news.title: Delhi: DDA allows power connections in colonies, villages regularised before October 2018
news.para: LG VK Saxena had recently directed DDA to issue an order in this regard. Earlier, he had received requests for power connection in such areas from all Delhi MPs, some MLAs and several resident welfare associations.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRCL to auction 4.2 acre land parcel in Nariman Point
news.para: The authority has already held initial discussions with leading global and domestic entities including the Blackstone Group, Hines, Mapletree Investments, Sumitomo Corp, the Tata Group, Lodha, K Raheja Corp, Oberoi Realty, and RMZ Group and has received a positive response for the same.

news.title: Midwest files draft IPO papers with Sebi to raise Rs 650 crore
news.para: The Hyderabad-based company's IPO is a mix of fresh issue of shares up to Rs 250 crore and an offer-for-sale (OFS) of up to Rs 400 crore by promoters. The offer also includes reservation for subscription by eligible employees, according to the draft papers filed on Monday.

news.title: JSW Cement adds two MTPA capacity at Vijayanagar plant
news.para: JSW Cement has increased its Vijayanagar plant capacity by 2 million tonnes per annum to 6 MTPA, bringing its total grinding capacity to 20.6 MTPA. This Rs 461 crore expansion is part of the company's goal to reach 40.85 MTPA through new and upgraded facilities across India.

news.title: SC allows NCLAT to consider NBCC's proposal for stalled Supertech projects
news.para: "Pendency of the present appeal and the present application will not come in the way of the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT) examining and deciding the proposal of the NBCC for the 17 projects of the corporate debtor (Supertech Ltd). Parties are at liberty to raise all pleas and contentions before the NCLAT," the bench said in its order.

news.title: Karnataka RERA issues Rs 707 crore recovery orders for delayed projects
news.para: While Lakshmanaraja and the other apartment buyers at the project in Thanisandra were promised they would get possession of their properties by 2019, nearly half the project is still incomplete.

news.title: Garuda Construction and Engineering sets price band at Rs 92-95 per share for its IPO
news.para: Garuda Construction and Engineering will open for subscription on October 8. In the IPO, approximately 35% is reserved for retail investors, 50% for qualified institutional buyers, and the remaining 15% for non-institutional investors.

news.title: REA Group ends takeover pursuit after multiple rejections from Britain's Rightmove
news.para: Australian property listing firm REA's decision to walk away from making a formal offer for Rightmove ahead of a 1600 GMT deadline capped a month-long saga that saw the London-listed firm rebuff four proposals on valuation concerns.

news.title: Goa government approves amendment disallowing change in use of comunidade land
news.para: CM Pramod Sawant said that there have been several instances where land granted, sold or allocated by the comunidade for a specific purpose, whether through sale, lease, emphyteusis, or leave and licence, as per the provisions of the code, has been used for other than the specified purpose.Goa government disallows change in use of comunidade land

news.title: Godrej Properties to raise Rs 6,000 crore through issue of securities
news.para: The fund raising could be in one or more tranches through public and/or private offerings including qualified institutions placement, rights issue, further public offer or any other mode as may be permitted under applicable laws and/or any combination thereof.

news.title: Rising land costs, approval delays hit new project launches and property sales
news.para: ​​However, total absorption surpassed new supply by 18%, reducing inventory by 15% during the quarter, according to PropEquity, a data analytics firm. Pune, Hyderabad and Kolkata saw the steepest declines of between 44% to 49% each.

news.title: New home prices in China rise 0.14% in September 2024
news.para: The average price across 100 cities edged up 0.14%, compared with the previous month's 0.11%, showed data released by property researcher China Index Academy.

news.title: PM-UDAY centres to operate seven days a week in Delhi: DDA
news.para: PM-UDAY Scheme is aimed at granting ownership rights to the residents of 1,731 unauthorised colonies in Delhi. The primary objective of this scheme is to provide legal recognition to residents' properties, by conferring ownership rights, the statement said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: SRFDCL eases bidding criteria to attract bidders for riverfront plots
news.para: The SRFDCL issued a request for proposal (RFP) for the sale of development rights for two riverfront plots. No international company showed interest. While the sale drew interest from two Mumbai companies and five from Gujarat, their representatives raised queries regarding the experience criteria and parking.

news.title: Home prices in Australia rise 0.4% in September 2024
news.para: Figures from property consultant CoreLogic, released on Tuesday, showed prices across the nation climbed 0.4% in September, in line with the 0.3% growth seen in July and August.

news.title: Maradu civic body seeks SC approval for new construction at demolition site
news.para: According to reports, SC had recently observed that the case against Maradu apartment complexes, which were found to have violated coastal regulation zone (CRZ) norms, should have been resolved by imposing a heavy fine on flat owners instead of demolition.
